    "is_duplicate": true,
    "duplicate_of": "019",
    "body": "<h1>Why Per-Minute Pricing Actually Protects Your Business</h1>\n<h2>The Problem Nobody Talks About</h2>\n<p>Most businesses evaluating voice AI get one thing wrong: they compare feature lists.</p>\n<p>Feature lists lie. Demos lie. What matters is what happens when a real customer calls at 8:47 PM and asks something that isn't in your FAQ.</p>\n<h2>Let Me Tell You a Story</h2>\n<p>When I started evaluating voice AI for my own business, I made every mistake possible. I compared feature lists. I watched polished demos. I asked about 'NLP accuracy' and 'latency benchmarks' — words that sound important but mean nothing to a customer calling your business.</p>\n<p>Then my co-founder asked me a simple question: 'Will this answer the phone when a confused customer calls at 9 PM and asks something that's not in our FAQ?'</p>\n<p>That's the only question that matters. Everything else is decoration.</p>\n<h2>What This Actually Means for Your Business</h2>\n<p><strong>What does transparent pricing mean in voice AI?</strong></p>\n<p>It means you know exactly what you pay per minute. No hidden setup fees. No 'enterprise pricing' that requires a 45-minute sales call to discover. No minimum commitments that lock you in for a year.</p>\n<p>At Speaksy, it's ₹2.5 per minute. All-inclusive. That's it. You use 100 minutes, you pay ₹250. You use 10,000 minutes, you pay ₹25,000.</p>\n<p><strong>Why per-minute pricing makes sense:</strong> You're not buying software licenses. You're buying conversations. And conversations are measurable. You can tie them directly to revenue: this call cost ₹15, it generated a ₹50,000 sale.</p>\n<p>That's not a cost. That's an investment with a clear ROI.</p>\n<h2>How to Actually Evaluate Voice AI ROI</h2>\n<p>Forget the fancy calculations. Here's simple math that any business owner can follow:</p>\n<p><strong>The cost side:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Speaksy charges ₹2.5 per minute</li>\n<li>Average call: 3-4 minutes = ₹7.5-10 per call</li>\n<li>1,000 calls = ₹7,500-10,000</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>The value side:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Each answered call = one customer who didn't hang up</li>\n<li>If 10% of those become customers worth ₹5,000 each = ₹5,00,000 revenue</li>\n<li>Cost to generate: ₹10,000</li>\n<li>ROI: 50x</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>But let's be conservative:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Say only 2% convert</li>\n<li>Say average order value is ₹2,000</li>\n<li>1,000 calls × 2% × ₹2,000 = ₹40,000 revenue</li>\n<li>Cost: ₹10,000</li>\n<li>ROI: 4x</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Even more conservative — just saved costs:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Human agent cost per call: ₹50-80 (salary + overhead)</li>\n<li>AI cost per call: ₹7.5-10</li>\n<li>Savings: ₹40-70 per call</li>\n<li>1,000 calls = ₹40,000-70,000 saved</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>The real ROI though?</strong> It's the customer at 9:47 PM who got an answer instead of voicemail. The lead who got called back in 30 seconds instead of 2 days. The patient whose appointment was confirmed at 7 AM.</p>\n<p>Some things don't fit in a spreadsheet. But they show up in your revenue.</p>\n<h2>Try This Simple Calculation for Your Business</h2>\n<p>Grab a calculator. Answer these 5 questions:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>How many calls do you get daily?</strong> (Check your phone logs)</li>\n<li><strong>How many do you answer?</strong> (Be honest)</li>\n<li><strong>How many are enquiries/sales leads?</strong> (Estimate)</li>\n<li><strong>What's your average order value?</strong> (You know this)</li>\n<li><strong>What's your conversion rate?</strong> (Leads who become customers)</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Now:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Unanswered calls × % that are leads × your conversion rate × average order value = <strong>Monthly revenue you're losing</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>100 calls/day × 40 unanswered = 40 missed calls</li>\n<li>50% are leads = 20 leads/day</li>\n<li>10% convert = 2 customers/day</li>\n<li>₹5,000 average order = ₹10,000/day lost</li>\n<li><strong>₹3 lakh/month in lost revenue</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>An AI voice agent costing ₹15,000-25,000/month that answers those 40 calls?</p>\n<p>That's not an expense. That's the best ROI you'll see this year.</p>\n<h2>The Bigger Picture</h2>\n<p><strong>The businesses winning in 2026 have figured something out:</strong> You don't need the fanciest app. You don't need the biggest marketing budget. You need to answer your phone. Every time. In every language. At any hour.</p>\n<p>Everything else is secondary.</p>\n<p><strong>Want to see how this works for your business?</strong></p>\n<p>Sign up at <a href=\"https://speaksy.in\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">speaksy.in</a>. You get 1 hour of free calling credits — no credit card, no sales call, no commitment. Test it on real calls. See if your customers can tell the difference.</p>\n<p>Most can't. And that's the whole point.</p>\n<hr>\n<h2>About the Author</h2>\n<p><strong>Sai Chaitanya</strong> — Co-founder &amp; Product at Speaksy</p>\n<p>Sai runs product at Speaksy. When he's not making voice AI sound less like robots and more like your neighbour, he's usually at some Hyderabad chai stall testing language models on unsuspecting chaiwallahs.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><em>Speaksy — AI voice agents that talk to India the way India actually talks.</em></p>\n<p><em>🇮🇳 Hinglish · Tanglish · Tenglish · Kanglish · Marathi-English · Indian English</em></p>\n<p><em>🌐 <a href=\"https://speaksy.in\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">speaksy.in</a> · 📞 AI voice agents for Indian businesses</em></p>"
